# fkwu.conf.example -- copy to `fkwu.conf` (read from the current directory at startup).
#
# The seed reads THIS file once, lazily, replacing the FK_* / FORM_* / MESH_* environment
# variables it used to read via getenv (env vars scatter; a config file is durable and reviewable).
# Absent file -> empty config -> every toggle at its default. Standard OS env vars we do not own
# (TMPDIR) still come from the environment.
#
# Line form:  KEY value   |   KEY=value   |   KEY   (bare key means on / "1")
# "KEY 0" explicitly disables. '#' begins a comment.

# --- observation ---
# FK_OBSERVE 1          # per-call ack witness ("offer fn.. args.. ack..") on stderr
# FK_MELT_WITNESS 1     # print a line each time the GC melts (compacts) the heap
# FK_READ_WITNESS 1     # print each read_file / read_file_slice host read

# --- startup / network ---
# FORM_KERNEL_STACK_MB 256   # main worker-thread stack size in MB
# MESH_RELAY host:port       # relay address for the mesh transport
